dataIdInfo.idAbs: The polygons in this shape file describe in graphical form the areas of applicability of geodetic data in the EPSG Dataset. Boundaries of geodetic data applicability are often indistinct. These polygons provide a coarse representation of these limits, complimenting textual descriptions in the Dataset. The polygons are also available as GML documents downloadable from the EPSG Registry. For further description of the area records in the Database please refer to OGP Geomatics guidance note 7 part 1, Using the EPSG Geodetic Dataset, available at http://info.ogp.org.uk/geomatics/guides/index.html.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This file contains polygons describing the areas of applicability of geodetic data in the EPSG Geodetic Parameter Dataset. The Dataset can be found at www.epsg-registry.org and www.epsg.org/geodetic.
dataIdInfo.idCredit:
The user assumes the entire risk as to the accuracy and the use of this data. The data may be used, copied and distributed subject to the conditions in the terms of use in http://info.ogp.org.uk/geomatics/CurrentDB.html.
Comments on the polygon data may be submitted to OGP through http://info.ogp.org.uk/geomatics/Comms/Comment.asp.
